sentences.english: The bus for the railroad station, I think it's no. 36.
sentences.chinese: 乘开往火车站的大众汽车，我想是36路吧。

sentences.english: After the merger, the German state is set to remain the second-biggest VW shareholder.
sentences.chinese: 合并后，这个州仍将是大众汽车的第二大股东。

sentences.english: Welcome to Volkswagen Beijing Center, enjoy original volkswagen service.
sentences.chinese: 大众汽车北京中心欢迎您，享受德国原版服务。

sentences.english: Volkswagen's unique construction keeps dampness out.
sentences.chinese: 大众汽车的独特构造，将潮润低档在外。

sentences.english: Volkswagen may be big, but judge them not by their size.
sentences.chinese: 大众汽车或许强大，但不要以个头称英雄。

sentences.english: Take Bus No. 21 and it will take you right there.
sentences.chinese: 坐21路大众汽车，它会带你到那边。

sentences.english: For a time, VW was the most valuable company in the world.
sentences.chinese: 以至于大众汽车一度成为世界上市值最高的公司。

sentences.english: As you well know, Volkswagen has given in to the Dark Side.
sentences.chinese: 就像你知道的那样，大众汽车已经沦落进了黑暗势力。

sentences.english: There's a really great one for Volkswagen.
sentences.chinese: 大众汽车有一则广告很不错。

sentences.english: The single seater aero car totes VW (Volkswagen) branding.
sentences.chinese: 这种流线型外形的单座车由大众汽车生产。

sentences.english: Look at the history of Volkswagen, the first small car.
sentences.chinese: 看看大众汽车的历史，第一个小型汽车品牌。
